news.title: Will file caveat in SC: Wave Group buyers after NCLAT order
news.para: Authority sources, however, said the developer may still apply for the restoration of the land and go for the reschedulement policy to clear dues and complete stalled projects.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA developing three more layouts for MIG
news.para: The VMRDA had to slash the price of the plots in its Palavalasa layout due to the poor response. The per square yard price was reduced to ₹14,500 from the earlier fixed ₹18,000 in the Palavalasa layout located near Anandapuram in Vizag suburbs.

news.title: KIIFB allots Rs 102 crore for land acquisition of Kochi metro phase II
news.para: Once the land acquisition is completed, Kochi Metro Rail Ltd (KMRL) will be able to initiate procedures for inviting tenders for construction of stations and Metro viaducts.

news.title: Complaint invalid if OC issued before RERA Act passed: Karnataka HC
news.para: The judge in the case pointed out that the project had lost its status as an ongoing project because the occupancy certificate had been issued prior to the act coming into effect. This means that the complainant, Shyama Shetty, cannot maintain a complaint against the developer, MS Provident Housing Limited, under the act.

news.title: Charge equally for registering agents, firms: HC to Haryana RERA
news.para: With this, the Haryana Real Estate Regulatory Authority (HRERA) can charge an equal amount from those registering themselves as real estate agents as an individual or a proprietary firm.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates defaults on Rs 4,059 crore loans
news.para: In September 2018, ICICI Bank filed an insolvency petition against JAL but the matter is still pending before the Allahabad bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT).

news.title: China Evergrande to hold talks with bondholders on January 11: Sources
news.para: Once China's top-selling developer, Evergrande is now at the centre of the country's property crisis. Its $22.7 billion of offshore debt, including loans and private bonds, is deemed to be in default after it missed payments late last year.

news.title: Glut of office space in Hyderabad has builders worried
news.para: While the city has at least 25 to 30 million square feet (sft) of ready-to-occupy office space dotting its IT corridor, another 50 million sft is in the pipeline that is set to come up in the next three years.

news.title: Assigned landowners likely to get full title: Andhra Pradesh Revenue Minister
news.para: He said that a high-level committee is studying the issue in different states and it is expected to submit its report very soon. He said that the government will take a call after going through the recommendations of the committee.

news.title: Will Gujarat government remove discrepancies while fixing new jantri rates?
news.para: The jantri rate is used to arrive at the value of properties at the time of their sale. As per the 2011 jantri rates, there is a vast difference in the value of properties on either side of the same road.

news.title: Second phase of Mumbai metro's 2A and 7 lines to be operational soon: MMRDA
news.para: The MMRDA will take a 16-hour mega block for the integration of the first phase of metro lines with the second phase between 6 am to 10 pm on January 8 on lines 2A and 7 for testing of integrated signalling systems.

news.title: Gujarat HC stays eviction of woman from GHB colony
news.para: Siddhi Developers and Builders issued eviction notices to people reluctant to vacate the premises after a single-judge bench in September 2022 paved the way for the redevelopment of 11 buildings in the society.

news.title: Madurai corporation plans centre to process construction waste
news.para: ​Civic activists say Madurai corporation needs a construction and demolition waste processing centre as in Chennai to solve the issue, which will also bring revenue to the corporation. The corporation is now planning to set up one.

news.title: Kolkata: 40,000 people living in 10,000 homes in Duttabad set to get addresses
news.para: Ward 38 of BMC from Thursday started marking the homes in the semi-slum area in Duttabad, which covers around 85 acres of land, bordering Salt Lake and EM Bypass.

news.title: CIDCO mass housing scheme applications' deadline extended to January 23
news.para: ​The state-run planning authority is offering these homes in Ulwe node in Navi Mumbai in Thane district for economical weaker sections (EWS) as part of the Centre's Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana (PMAY), he said.
